description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;COMMUNITY COMPLEX CARE TEAM&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you committed to delivering high standards of individualised patient care? Are you frustrated because you don’t have enough time to spend with your clients? Then come and join our rapidly developing and exciting service. We are a team of dedicated qualified nurses and care staff who provide comprehensive care for adults and children with continuing, complex health care/ high dependency nursing needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our patients have specialist care requirements (for example, ventilation/ tracheostomy care) and need one to one care, full training and on going support will be provided for the right applicants.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will be expected to work flexibly over 7 days on a rota across a range of shifts. Previous care experience is essential (child/ health/ or social care experience). Ability to work as part of a team is essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;COMPLEX CARE SUPPORT WORKER – Band 2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base: Lichfield (East) &lt;/strong&gt;Working Location could cover Lichfield / Tamworth / Burton / Cannock&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;BAND 2 £18,005 to £19,337 plus enhancements for any unsociable hours worked as per Agenda for Change Terms and Conditions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part time or Full time hours considered - to be worked flexibly.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The main focus of the post will be to provide one to one care for a patient with complex health needs in their home or a community setting. Healthcare and/ or Nursery Nurse experience and an NVQ Level 2 qualification or equivalent is essential. Working towards a level 2 qualification would also be considered. The successful applicant will have 24/7 support from qualified staff.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are committed to safeguarding children and vulnerable adults and all successful applicants will have an enhanced and barred list disclosure check performed prior to appointment.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information about this post please contact Ryan Rukas on 07530 975635 or 01543 442042&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Children’s services in Midlands Partnership NHS Foundation Trust are committed to using evidence from Outcome Measures and Feedback Tools to support our efforts to help children and young people to fulfil their potential. You will have a responsibility to support and promote the use of such measures.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
